node.text: While many events have had to be cancelled this year, trans actor, writer and director @jake_graf5 shows us how him and his family are still celebrating Pride at home. How lovely do they all look in our #FeelingProud collection?! 💜  This year, we’re proud to continue to support @ilgaworld with a £150,000 donation, helping in their mission for LGBTQI+ equality. Head to primark.com to find out more #Primark #PrideMonth

node.text: You may have heard that we've launched a collection of period underwear! The lovely @francescaperks and @charlotteemilyprice put them to the test to let you know more about how they work. These are a comfortable and convenient solution that are designed to work for you; we at Primark understand the diversities in bodies and period flows so while our period underwear is designed to replace tampons, cups and pads, it may also be worn with these products for extra protection. Head to primark.com to find out more #Primark

node.text: Our collection of period underwear is designed to help you tackle your period with ease, and in comfort. Wanna know a bit more about how they work/what they're like IRL? The lovely @livblankson gives them a try and shares her verdict. Ranging from £6/€7 for a single pair, up to £16/€19 for a multipack, these are a super affordable, reusable and planet friendly alternative to other sanitary products ✨ #Primark

node.text: This month on #PrimarkSpotlight, we meet the incredibly talented singer/songwriter @iamkyami. Originally from New York, Kyami has lived in the UK for three and a half years and currently writes, produces, performs and DJs (just to name a few). Kyami chats to us about finding empowerment within her true sound and pushing through failures to find successes. On a chilled Friday vibe? Make sure you go and check out 'IAmKyami' on Spotfiy for the ultimate soundtrack to match your mood ✨ #Primark #FeelGoodFriday

node.text: It's so good to see you all again in England and Wales! node.text: This month, we meet the lovely @dani_durrett, an amazing artist with the Boston Ballet. Not only does Daniel's talent shine through, but his determination, positivity and drive to succeed, no matter the obstacle, has got us feeling motivated to go and smash the next goal. Feeling like dance could be for you? Daniel says 'dance is for everyone - just put some music on and let your body do the talking' and we couldn't love that phrase more. Was lovely to meet you, Daniel! Thanks for reminding us to never give up on our goals 🙌 #PrimarkSpotlight

node.title: The Primark Spotlight with dance artist @dani_durrett 💫
